pg_tre (1.3.0-dev-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Vendor sparsemap 2.3.0 (drop-in compatible upgrade from 2.2.0).
    Hardening-only release: bounds clamping in __sm_chunk_get_position
    and sm_contains, bounds-safe chunk walker in __sm_get_size_impl,
    NULL tolerance in sm_contains, UBSan fix in the diagnostic path.
  * No on-disk format changes; no re-index required.

 -- Greg Burd <greg@burd.me>  Thu, 14 May 2026 14:00:00 +0000

pg_tre (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Vendor sparsemap 2.2.0 (drop-in compatible upgrade from 2.0.0).
  * Adopt sparsemap's allocator-friendly APIs: sm_open_copy,
    sm_add_grow, sm_next_member.
  * Fix multi-leaf right-link sm_union reversed-logic bug that
    silently dropped every leaf past the first.  Same on-disk
    format as 1.0.0; no re-index required.
  * Gate per-tuple bloom and positional filter on
    pg_tre.tuple_bloom_enable until the chain-rank lookup is
    repaired; executor recheck remains authoritative.

 -- Greg Burd <greg@burd.me>  Thu, 14 May 2026 10:00:00 +0000

pg_tre (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release candidate.
  * Native PostgreSQL 18+ index access method for approximate regex.
  * Three-tier filter funnel: range bloom, sparsemap trigram postings,
    per-tuple bloom.
  * Ships legacy tre_amatch() UDFs for compatibility.

 -- Greg Burd <greg@burd.me>  Tue, 12 May 2026 10:00:00 +0000
